00:05:58.940 --> 00:06:04.320
So the first question is why
Early Modern Globalization?

00:06:04.320 --> 00:06:09.680 position:56%
Because usually we think
globalization either began yesterday

00:06:09.680 --> 00:06:13.520
eighty-nine or something
or is simply a continuation

00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:18.290
of modern Western hegemony,
modernization to entire globe.

00:06:18.290 --> 00:06:24.870
So it was meant Early Modern to
challenge precisely our modernist

00:06:24.870 --> 00:06:27.750
and Eurocentric assumptions
that assumed

00:06:27.750 --> 00:06:29.460
that everything begins
with modernity.

00:06:29.460 --> 00:06:32.000
There was tradition before
then there is modernity,

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:35.050
and everything happened before
is basically irrelevant.

00:06:35.050 --> 00:06:38.910
And globalization is simply
supposed to be simply an expansion

00:06:38.910 --> 00:06:41.360
of modernization to the globe,

00:06:41.360 --> 00:06:45.580
by pointing out that there was
Early Modern Globalization before

00:06:45.580 --> 00:06:49.520
modernity, before Western
hegemony it means the dynamic

00:06:49.520 --> 00:06:54.250
of Globalization cannot be
understood simply is a continuation

00:06:54.250 --> 00:06:57.010
of Western modernity.

00:06:57.010 --> 00:07:02.860
So the question is,
Globalization can only be defined

00:07:02.860 --> 00:07:06.200
in the most abstract
in general terms,

00:07:06.200 --> 00:07:08.200
precisely because if
you defined completely,

00:07:08.200 --> 00:07:12.300
you will define only part
of it, a period of it or one

00:07:12.300 --> 00:07:16.490
which is characterized by economic
or by politics or by cultures.

00:07:16.490 --> 00:07:20.550
So it can only be defined
in abstract

00:07:20.550 --> 00:07:24.510
in general terms is the
process through which the world,

00:07:24.510 --> 00:07:28.130
the entire globe becomes
a single place

00:07:28.130 --> 00:07:32.650
with increasing global connectivity
between peoples, societies,

00:07:32.650 --> 00:07:39.060 position:56%
and cultures with humanity attaining
and increasing global consciousness.

00:07:39.060 --> 00:07:44.020
Now Globalization proper and that's
why Early Modern Globalization

00:07:44.020 --> 00:07:48.690
begins only once the
circumnavigations of the globe

00:07:48.690 --> 00:07:53.070
in the early modern era
after 1492 made possible

00:07:53.070 --> 00:07:56.530
for the first time both
global connectivity

00:07:56.530 --> 00:07:58.040
and global consciousness.

00:07:58.040 --> 00:08:01.180
Of course there were
connectivity before all of Asia,

00:08:01.180 --> 00:08:05.950
in Africa had been connected for
millennia, certainly for centuries

00:08:05.950 --> 00:08:09.180
at least the Axial
age and the Axial age

00:08:09.180 --> 00:08:13.870
to a certain extent all the great
cultures already anticipated a

00:08:13.870 --> 00:08:16.110
global consciousness,
a global humanity,

00:08:16.110 --> 00:08:20.200
some kind of ethical universalism
or logical universalism.

00:08:20.200 --> 00:08:23.480
But this anticipation
only becomes a reality

00:08:23.480 --> 00:08:26.180
with precisely the
global connectivity

00:08:26.180 --> 00:08:28.700
and the global consciousness
made possible

00:08:28.700 --> 00:08:35.460
by the early modern
circumnavigations of the globe.

00:08:35.460 --> 00:08:39.480
Globalization therefore is a
process, a complex process,

00:08:39.480 --> 00:08:44.380
it cannot be reduced to any single
factor, an uneven process namely,

00:08:44.380 --> 00:08:48.190
it happens differently in
different parts of the globe

00:08:48.190 --> 00:08:52.090
at different rates, at different
times affecting differently

00:08:52.090 --> 00:08:55.730
different peoples, so it's not
an even process across the globe,

00:08:55.730 --> 00:08:57.750
it is the multidimensional process.

00:08:57.750 --> 00:09:03.200
It can only be defined unlike,
neither is world capitalism

00:09:03.200 --> 00:09:07.540
or world geopolitics or simply
a world technology in the sense

00:09:07.540 --> 00:09:11.900
of mass media and is
experienced differently

00:09:11.900 --> 00:09:14.990
by different people
in different places.

00:09:14.990 --> 00:09:20.730 position:56%
